Ali was hospitalized December 20 with what was initially believed to be a mild case of pneumonia. 

Doctors later determined Ali was suffering from a severe urinary tract infection and not pneumonia, Gunnell said.

He said the Ali family appreciates the outpouring of support and well wishes.

Ali appeared in public in September at a ceremony in his hometown of Louisville for the Muhammad Ali Humanitarian Awards. Ali did not speak to the crowd but posed for photos with award winners, including former NFL great Jim Brown.

Brown leaned over and whispered to the seated Ali during the photo session. Later, Brown said he told Ali: 'You're the greatest of all time.' 

Ali and his wife, Lonnie, have homes in Paradise Valley, Arizona; Berrien Springs, Michigan; and in Louisville. Gunnell would not say which of his homes Ali had returned to.

